at|^b@2|at|^^|cp|3|at|^b^*bHoward Schutzman: ^*n|
cp||at|I agree with Cohen in principle. However, I am slightly more precise. I like to play negative doubles through 3@s, meaning a double of an opponent's overcall through 3@s shows support for the unbid major. Starting at the 4-level doubles are "card showing" but do not promise any particular distribution. They are neither purely penalty nor purely takeout. They mean "partner, do something intelligent". The more distributional partner is the more partner should want to bid. The flatter partner is, the more partner should want to pass.|
